track_notes: A rarely visited summit looking at the ground. No support on summit for a pole so take a guying ring or stake. Follow sheep paths alongside beck (with small waterfalls in places) up Penangus Hope. A little tussocky but a nice walk. Return same way I would suggest.

THe route starts from Carewoodrig which is also on the road to Roan Fell GM/SS-132. There are wide enough verges to park here. 

Sorry the start looses a bit of height but then steadily works up to the summit. There is a cain on the way but the summit is not marked.

There are good open views on the way to the summit. 

Time taken about 1 hour.
track_title: From the South East starting at Carewoodrig to Ellson Fell
